         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2009_81_EC>
               <PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
                  <D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                     <D_TECHNICAL/>
                  </D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>The works/goods/services can be provided only by a particular tenderer for reasons that are: technical.</P>
                     <P>The United Kingdom Ministry of Defence (the "Authority") intends to place an extension to contract CSA/3044 with BAE Systems Limited (the "Company") for the In-Service Support, including maintenance, repair and replacement component spares of Navigation Compass Stabilizer equipment fitted to current Naval platforms and other land-based facilities. The term of the extension is envisaged to be 1 year (with an option for the Authority to extend the contract for an additional 2 years).</P>
                     <P>It is considered that this contract extension can be placed using the negotiated procedure without prior publication of a contract notice pursuant to Article 28(1)(e) of Directive 2009/81/EC (Regulation 16(1)(a)(ii) of Defence and Security Public Contracts Regulations 2011) for technical reasons.</P>
                     <P>This is because:</P>
                     <P>1) Each of the Royal Navy’s platforms must have a navigational system capability that is fit for purpose at all times before they can be deployed in order to fulfil their roles. The Naval Compass Stabilizer (NCS) Mk1 equipment is either fitted as a single or dual system and provides Primary and Secondary Weapons Stabilisation/Heading reference. These systems also provide a Tertiary reference some platforms in the event that their main method of providing this information fails;</P>
                     <P>2) There is strict technical impracticability for a candidate other than the Company to achieve the required goals of maintaining and repairing the equipment. This is because only the Company, as the original system designer and equipment manufacturer, has at its disposal the specialist know how, extensive technical knowledge and maintenance history of the products and the characteristics of the system(s) being maintained;</P>
                     <P>3) The Company has developed in-house Special To Type (STT) Test equipment that is required to maintain, repair, fit and Set to Work the NCS Mk 1 equipment.</P>
                     <P>The Authority has already competed its requirement for a replacement system, and this contract extension is required as in interim measure to maintain the existing NCS1 system until the replacement is effective.</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
            </DIRECTIVE_2009_81_EC>
